Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search                  Help     Search   Search   Expand search box              Help Search Results           Search for articles, databases and journals    You can search for articles in databases and journals. Databases search many journals in a discipline or subject.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Visit Special Collections and University Archives    Two reading rooms are dedicated to researchers using our collections. View Special Collections and University Archives hours at Daley Library or Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago .    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago             Use an archival finding aid    A “finding aid” describes the contents of an archival collection. It is the first thing to look at before handling a collection at Special Collections and University Archives.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago             Find an archival collection    UIC Special Collections and University Archives holds a variety of materials that are available to researchers and we offer several resources to aid you in your search.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago             Recommend an item for the library to purchase    Is there a book, DVD or other item you think UIC should own? Provide as much information on the item as you can and give your personal contact information if you want to be the first in line to borrow it.  NOTE: Requests will be held until July 2020. The library cannot purchase materials until July because all I-Share libraries are migrating to a new library system. We regret the inconvenience.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Get textbooks    You can find textbooks for some courses in the Library, but you may have to buy or rent a required edition for your class. Search for textbooks in the Library Catalog.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Use other non-UIC libraries    UIC students, faculty and staff can visit several academic and research libraries in Illinois and the Chicago area. You are able to enter some libraries by showing your UIC i-card or registering with the library. You can also request books for pick up at UIC through the I-Share Catalog. Materials from institutions that are not part of I-Share can usually be borrowed through interlibrary loan .    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Request items    Staff, students, faculty and emeritus faculty can request items from other libraries. I-Share will quickly deliver physical items from Illinois academic libraries. Interlibrary Loan (ILLiad) will allow you to request scanned articles and items not available in I-Share.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Report that an item is missing    If you’re looking for an item and it is not on the shelf, please stop at a service desk to let a staff member know. This helps us to locate or replace the missing item and keep our catalog up to date. If you need an item that is missing, you may request items from other libraries.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Search for books and e-books    Use the Library Search on the home page to find books and media. You can also search the UIC Library catalog .    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Get books from storage    You can request books to be delivered from storage for pick up at your library location through the Library Catalog or in person.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Faculty services    The library can support UIC faculty in their teaching, research and publishing efforts and with Library collections and e-resources.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Alumni services    If you graduated from UIC or John Marshall Law School and live in Illinois, you may be eligible for an Alumni Borrowing card to continue to check out materials from the Library.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana          Filter by Location     Chicago-Daley     Chicago-Health Sciences     Peoria-Health Sciences     Rockford-Health Sciences     Urbana-Health Sciences     Apply f